            Unfortunately, Jökull can no longer maintain it and so decided
            %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/calepinapp/status/192335906479415296"} to close shop in June.
            He
            %a{:href => "http://github.com/jokull/calepin"} open-sourced the project,
            tho.  If anyone wants to pick it up…
          %p
            Being no stranger to the blogging game, I know all of my options, but I gotta say, Calepin's concept (single files in Dropbox + push-button publishing via the website) really appealed to me more than the everything-in-Github-and-publish-via-Terminal way.  I'd switch to Calepin-contender
            %a{:href => "http://scriptogr.am/"} Scriptogram
            in an instant if they would allow for more flexibility in their blogs' URL paths.
          %p
